RTCIceParameters.summary: The RTCIceParameters dictionary specifies the username fragment and password assigned to an ICE session.

remarks.para: During ICE negotiation, each peer's username fragment and password are recorded in an RTCIceParameters object, which can be obtained from the by calling its or method, depending on which end interests you.

RTCIceParametersPassword.summary:
The
dictionary's password property specifies the ICE
password that, in tandem with the , uniquely identifies an ICE session for its entire
duration.
RTCIceParametersPassword.value:
A string containing the password that corresponds to the transport's
usernameFragment string

RTCIceParametersUsernameFragment.summary:
The dictionary's
usernameFragment property specifies the username fragment
("ufrag") that uniquely identifies the corresponding ICE session for the duration of the
current ICE session.
RTCIceParametersUsernameFragment.value:
A string containing the username fragment that, in tandem with the
, uniquely identify the ICE session
being used by the transport. The string may be up to 256 characters long.See to learn more about username
fragments and their role in a connection.
